The paper discusses Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) applications. The paper proposes a novel convergence metric for GANs using game theory concepts, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper uses various test scenarios to verify the validity of the proposed metric, which could fall under the category of game theory (cs.GT).
